Improve the layout of the Downloads dialog.

? `gophers:` support.

Make downloads directory location configurable.

Find a way to indicate when implicit page rendering is ongoing, and when it's
complete.  It's not usually a problem for text pages, but images sometimes take
a while to transfer, and it's not obvious what progress is being made.  This is
tricky to implement, because the embedded image support is provided by the JVM,
which doesn't expose any hooks that I can find to allow it to be monitored.

Add clickable links to in-line images within Markdown documents. At present,
we just get the image, so there's no way to do anything with it.

Catch redirect loops. Easy-ish to do, but I just haven't gotten to it.

? Find a way to supply emoji fonts internally. This isn't easy, unless I want to 
apply a font to every single element of the document viewer in code. And even
this it might not work -- Java Swing is funny about this kind of thing.

